(a) Listing and explanation of Sources of funds available to Adamu to finance the business :
Trade credit: Adamu can obtain products on credit terms from the producer and pay later.
II. Personal savings: Adamu could use his reserved income for uncertainties to start the business.
III. Gifts from families and friends: He could receive financial assistance from his friends and family members through the launch of the business opening to encourage him in the starting of the business;
IV. Hire purchase: Adamu can get some of the furniture and fittings for his shop on hire purchase to start his business;
V. Bank Joan: Adamu can take a loan from the bank at a particular interest rate to finance the business;
VI. Co-operative loan: He could take a loan from his cooperative society at a low interest rate to start the business;
VII. Bank overdraft: Adamu can get an overdraft from his bank at a particular interest rate to start the business by withdrawing more than his savings
